# Here comes the "top pond" with ten women.
# The labels are transcribed separately as f75v.L1
# Labels on nymphs in the top pond
# The picture suggests a water stream splashing on an elongated
# pond with two small posts, one shaped like a stubby cross.
# From the pond, ten ruvulets fall on ten naked nymphs,
# who are standing ankle-deep in an elongated tub.
# There are two lines of text just above the nymphs, broken into
# ten words by the rivulets ("-" below).
# They have been transcribed below as ten pairs of words,
# each pair in two lines. But who knows...
# Some of Grove's [kt] restored to [pf] based on other versions -JS.

# The picture resembles a lower pond sunk into the ground,
# fed by a tube from the tub further up the page.
# The pond is packed with 19 naked nymphs, ankle-deep in the water.
# There is a normal-looking paragraph on the right side of the pond.
# On the left side there are about 6 words at the top, apparently
# not aligned with the text, and presumed to be labels (below).
